<attr name="text"><![CDATA[h3. ParquetReadWrite

This example demonstrates reading and writing data in parquet format useing the ParquetReader and ParquetWriter components. 

* In phase 0, a DataGenerator component generates a single record which is then sent to the ParquetWriter component.
* The format of the record written to parquet is autogenerated from the metadata assigned to the edge. This can be refined using the {{Parquet Schema}} property of the ParquetWriter. Here the {{pairAmount}} field is explicitly set to to be written into the parquet file as DECIMAL.
* In phase 1, two ParquetReader components read the parquet file written in phase 0. With the first [ParquetReader|element://PARQUET_READER], the metadata on the output edge is automatically defined based on the specifed parquet file.  With the second  [ParquetReader|element://PARQUET_READER1], the output metadata is explicily defined to be a subset of the parquet file metadata, allowing the data job to read only specific fields.]]></attr>
</RichTextNote>
